Algorithm

Algorithm: 0/1 Knapsack (Dynamic Programming)

Input:
Number of items n, arrays profit[] and weight[], and knapsack capacity W.

Initialize:
Create a 2D array K[n+1][W+1].

For i = 0 to n
a. For w = 0 to W
  • If i == 0 or w == 0, then K[i][w] = 0
  • Else if weight[i-1] <= w
    → K[i][w] = max(profit[i-1] + K[i-1][w - weight[i-1]], K[i-1][w])
  • Else
    → K[i][w] = K[i-1][w]

Output:
K[n][W] → maximum achievable profit.
